Cell.Text: G|Speak with Miss Salma, if you wish to speak.
G|I grow tired of debating this. If Miss Salma insists on this folly, so be it.
G|I admit, there is strength in numbers. Perhaps between us...
What's going on here?
We should be inside, loading up on treasure. Worry-scales here thinks we should wait, though. Don't get any ideas, either. We were here first.
What's going on?
I don't care what Beem says. It's high time we get in there and find our fortune.
Gold, silver. Gems, maybe? Only one way to find out!

Node.Caption: dunIronbindInvestigate01: What do you expect to find inside?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Not without us, you aren't! I'm sure there's enough for everyone, after all. | Come on, Beem-Ja. We're going.

Node.Caption: dunIronbindSalmaProposal: I don't know about you, but I'm going in there.

Cell.Text: G|We're in this together. Stay close.
G|This is no time for idle talk.
G|Not now. Stay alert.
G|Let's clear the place out first. Then we'll gather our loot.
G|Eyes open. Danger could be anywhere.
G|This place is sure to make us rich!
Fool. I should thank you. I knew the girl wouldn't be strong enough to help me kill Gathrik alone.

[S] G|There's just one more thing I need from you. To fully absorb Gathrik's power I require a blood sacrifice. | Your blood should be good enough. This will go easier for us both if you don't bother fighting back.
I don't know. Beem-Ja has looked after me since I was knee-high to him. I need to rest, and then I think I'm going back to High Rock.
G|Go on without me. I think I need to be alone for a while.
Look, I never needed treasure. My father owns land; our family is wealthy. I just wanted adventure. Not this.

Node.Caption: dunIronbindSalmaPostTreasureTopic: Don't you want your treasure? Riches, and all that?

Cell.Text: Father never trusted Beem. I always thought he was just being overprotective.
